
[1]jester

   JEST'ER, n. A person given to jesting, sportive talk and merry pranks.

   --He rambled up and down

   With shallow jesters.

   1. One given to sarcasm.

   Now, as a jester, I accost you.

   2. A buffoon; a merry-andrew, a person formerly retained by princes to
   make sport for them.
